3.20	Lephalale	Lephalale	Lephalale or Ellisras is a coal mining town in the Limpopo province of South Africa immediately north of the Waterberg Massif. The town was established as Ellisras in 1960 and named after the original farm owners, Patrick Ellis and Piet Erasmus. In 2002, Ellisras was renamed Lephalale by the provincial government of Limpopo, after the main river that crosses the municipality. Lephalale is divided into three main subsections, Lephalale, Onverwacht and Marapong.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Blank_map_of_Limpopo_%282011%29.svg/250px-Blank_map_of_Limpopo_%282011%29.svg.png
